The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

                                        Archives
                                                   All eyes on Pampa, Arun

      A STAFF REPORTER
           
	Calcutta: Pune-based Army Sports Institute (ASI) runners will lead a field around 125 runners in the main event of the fourth Airtel Calcutta Marathon to be held here on Sunday. 
    
	While Arun Mahato and Pampa Chanda will spearhead the Bengal challenge. Pampa won the last years womens half marathon while Mahato finished eighth. 
    
	Besides the full marathon of 42.195km for men there will be a half marathon of 10.5km for women. 
    
	The prize money for the event has been increased to Rs 10.21 lakh compared to last years Rs 8.5 lakh. The mens winner will be richer by Rs 3 lakh while the womens top finisher will receive Rs 1 lakh. 
    
	The marathon will be flagged off near the basketball tent on Red Road at 7.30 am. The marathon will then proceed towards Maniktala, EM Bypass, Nicco Park, Gariahat, Jadavpur, Tollygunge Phari, Rashbehari Avenue, New Alipore before winding up at the starting point. 
                                                   
